  "prompt": "If you had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, what would you do?",
  "response": "If I had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, I would focus on maximizing my impact on the world, fulfilling personal dreams, and ensuring my loved ones are cared for. Here\u2019s how I might approach it:\n\n### 1. **Philanthropy and Legacy (60%)**\n   - **$1.8 billion** would go toward solving global challenges:\n     - Fighting poverty and hunger (e.g., funding sustainable agriculture, food distribution).\n     - Combating climate change (e.g., renewable energy projects, reforestation).\n     - Supporting education and healthcare in underserved communities.\n   - **Establish a foundation** to ensure the work continues after I\u2019m gone.\n\n### 2. **Personal Fulfillment and Experiences (20%)**\n   - **$600 million** would be spent on living life to the fullest:\n     - Traveling the world, experiencing different cultures, and seeing natural wonders.\n     - Pursuing passions like learning new skills, art, or creative projects.\n     - Hosting gatherings with friends and family to create lasting memories.\n\n### 3. **Loved Ones and Security (15%)**\n   - **$450 million** would ensure the well-being of family and friends:\n     - Setting up trust funds or investments to secure their futures.\n     - Paying off debts or mortgages for loved ones.\n     - Organizing meaningful experiences or trips to spend quality time together.\n\n### 4. **Personal Comfort and Fun (5%)**\n   - **$150 million** would go toward personal indulgence:\n     - Purchasing a luxurious home or yacht for comfort and enjoyment.\n     - Buying dream items like rare art, collectibles, or high-end experiences.\n     - Supporting causes or hobbies that bring me joy.\n\n### 5. **Final Projects and Reflection**\n   - Write a memoir or create a documentary to share my story and lessons learned.\n   - Fund a personal passion project, like building a community center or a museum.\n\nBy focusing on philanthropy, personal growth, and relationships, I\u2019d aim to leave a positive legacy while making the most of the time I have left.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
